Xinhua Commentary: Turn outstanding returning migrant workers into a new force for rural revitalization-Xinhuanet
Talents are the key to rural revitalization.
Where to find talent?
Outstanding returning migrant workers are an indispensable new force.
Xinhua News Agency issued Hai Chunzuo
Xinhua News Agency, Chengdu, July 26th. Title: Turning outstanding returning migrant workers into a new force for rural revitalization
Zhang Xiong, 34, lives in Guoyuan Village, Meishan City, Sichuan. In 2010, he quit his job in Beijing with a monthly salary of tens of thousands and returned home to start a business.
After several years of hard work, the annual income of the grape-growing family farm he runs now exceeds one million yuan, and he has become a well-known leader in getting rich. He has also been selected into the village's " two committees " team.
In recent years, inspired by a series of policies to support agriculture and benefit agriculture, such as national poverty alleviation and rural revitalization, more and more outstanding migrant workers like Zhang Xiong have chosen to return home to start their own businesses, activating a pool of spring water in the countryside.
Sichuan, a province with a large population in western China and a large labor export province, has implemented the " Outstanding Migrant Workers Return Training Project " according to the situation. In 2019 alone, more than 8,000 village party branch secretaries will be generated from the outstanding migrant workers, 61,000 village reserve forces will be cultivated, and more than 20,000 party members will be developed, providing a strong guarantee for winning the fight against poverty and implementing the rural revitalization strategy.
To achieve initial prosperity in the countryside, it is essential to raise rural living standards and particularly those of impoverished villagers.
Since the reform and opening up, a large number of young and middle-aged laborers in rural China have gone out to work to increase their income, and some have established their own enterprises through hard work.
However, objectively, it has also led to the emergence of " hollowing " to varying degrees in rural areas, especially the weakening of rural grass-roots organizations. Village party branch secretaries and party members all show the characteristics of " one old and one low" , that is, aging, low academic qualifications, weak leaders of village party organizations, and outstanding problems.
If rural talents and other factors have been flowing unidirectionally to the cities, and the countryside has been in a state of " blood loss " and " anemia " for a long time, revitalization is empty talk.
Attract those migrant workers who are capable, conscious and interested in serving their hometowns, guide them to return home to start businesses and become rich leaders, train them to become party members and rural cadres on the basis of merit, and enrich the ranks of grass-roots cadres. This is the fundamental solution to the problem that rural party members and grass-roots party organizations are not connected with each other.
Excellent migrant workers can be attracted back, but they must be kept and done well.
In recent years, Sichuan has started by paying close attention to the party building of migrant workers. On the basis of strict selection criteria, it has established institutional mechanisms such as directional referral, service guarantee, training and promotion, selection and use of outstanding migrant workers, so that they can improve their abilities, have security in their work, have hope in their lives, truly take root in rural areas, and have a sense of accomplishment in starting a business.
This year is the end of the decisive battle against poverty. Talents are the key factor in the connection between poverty alleviation and rural revitalization.
Party committees and governments at all levels should attach great importance to the group of outstanding returning migrant workers, and through comprehensive measures, turn them into a task force and a new force that can stay, fight and cannot be taken away, so as to provide strong organizational guarantee and talent support for rural poverty alleviation, well-off development and revitalization.
