Beijing's natural ecology continues to improve, attracting more than 500 species of wild animals to " settle " in the city-chinanews.com
2020-07-26 05: 03: 17 Source: Beijing Youth Daily Author: Wang Sishuo Editor: Wang Sishuo
The natural ecology of the capital continues to improve, attracting wildlife cities to " settle down "
More than 500 species of wild animals in Beijing
(Reporter Wang Bin) A reporter from Beijing Youth Daily learned from the Municipal Bureau of Landscaping and Greening that in recent years, with the continuous improvement of the capital's natural ecological environment, the types and numbers of wild animals have also continued to increase.
At present, the number of terrestrial vertebrate wild animals inhabiting Beijing has increased to more than 500 species, including national first-class protected animals such as brown pheasant and black stork, as well as national second-class protected animals such as goral, swan, gray crane and mandarin duck.
Whether planted into urban forests everywhere in the Second Ring Road or embedded in small and micro wetlands between buildings, it not only brings the wildness of nature to the citizens of the capital, but also attracts wild animals to " settle " in the city.
In midsummer, Songshan National Nature Reserve, located in the Yanshan Mountains in the northwest of Yanqing District, is full of vitality.
A raccoon was playing leisurely by the mountain stream, while two badgers were fighting with each other.
Looking back, a wild boar couldn't help scratching and rubbing against the bark. Hu Qiaoli, director of the Songshan National Nature Reserve Management Office, said that by the end of 2019, there were 178 species of wild animals living in this green sea with a total area of more than 6,200 hectares, including the national first-class protected animal golden eagle and the national second-class protected animal spoon chicken and impala. Nearly one third of the city's wild animal species can be found here.
" In Songshan, wild animals are the real' masters', and our staff can only be regarded as the' bodyguards' of others at best. "
Hu Qiaoli said that in order to understand the situation of wildlife in the reserve on the spot, there are more than 30 professional patrol members every day to patrol along 16 carefully formulated protection routes, and there will be a " big circle " every month, spending a whole day almost all over the reserve.
" During inspections, we should not only check and record biodiversity, but also check and install artificial bird nests, rescue injured wild animals, install field infrared cameras and so on. "
More than 200 infrared cameras have been installed in Songshan National Nature Reserve to record the living conditions of wild animals in the forest.
Hu Qiaoli said that with the continuous enrichment of biodiversity in the reserve in recent years, more and more wild animals have appeared in the camera, leopard cats, raccoon dogs and pig badgers have become " resident guests" , and the " appearance rate " of the national second-class protected animal impala is also getting higher and higher.
Zhang Zhiming, director of the Wildlife and Wetland Protection Division of the Beijing Municipal Bureau of Landscaping and Greening, said that the number of terrestrial vertebrate wild animals in Beijing has increased from 461 in 1994 to more than 500 now, and the species and number of wild animals in Beijing have continued to increase in recent years.
Wild animals are becoming more and more common in cities, which is closely related to the continuous upgrading of greening in the capital city in recent years.
In particular, the new round of afforestation and greening construction of one million mu, which began in 2018, proposes to reshape the urban ecological environment, enhance the ecological function of woodland and green space, and highlight the concept of " near nature. "
The planning strives to achieve interconnection and interaction with the surrounding green space, so as to facilitate wild animals to " visit relatives and friends" , and the trees planted are also honey and food plants that animals love.
Black land " grows " agricultural modernization-Xinhuanet
Xinhua News Agency, Harbin, July 26. Title: Black land " grows " agricultural modernization
In midsummer, two spraying planes passed by the 10,000-mu high-yield demonstration field in the second operation station of the fifth management area of Youyi Farm, forming two white lines. The words " the first field in the world " planted with black rice seedlings in the green fields were particularly eye-catching.
Kong Lingqiang, the head of the operation station, said that this kind of aircraft can spray chemicals on more than 6,000 acres of cultivated land a day, and the efficiency is about 8 times that of drones and hundreds of times that of humans.
This farm is located in Youyi County, Heilongjiang Province, China's largest grain-producing province. From the sound of rice cutting in the past to the sound of " rumbling " today, traditional Chinese farming and farms have transformed in this black soil belt.
In addition to airplanes, satellites are also used in the modern agricultural production of Friendship Farm.
Kong Lingqiang introduced that on the one hand, they use satellite remote sensing technology to achieve accurate fertilization, reduce agricultural input and reduce pollution; on the other hand, satellite navigation technology can improve the standardized operation level of agricultural machinery in the field.
In the process of rice production this year, the farm expanded the operating area of satellite navigation unmanned transplanting technology from 3,000 mu last year to 30,000 mu.
This technology makes seedling planting more uniform, maximizes the utilization of sunlight and cultivated land resources, and saves 16 yuan in labor costs per mu.
The farm tried new technologies such as informatization and intelligence in agricultural production, and formed the largest agricultural machinery group in China from the ground to the sky.
According to statistics, the total number of farm machinery is 49,000 units (pieces), and the comprehensive mechanization rate in the field is 99.8%.
Agricultural machinery operations achieve 100% GPS satellite navigation, 100% precision seeding in dry fields, and 100% high-horsepower locomotive operations in dry fields.
" Green agriculture, smart agriculture and digital agriculture are the exploration directions of agricultural modernization. "
Liu Hualian, director of Friendship Farm, said.
The key to agricultural modernization lies in scientific and technological progress.
Heilongjiang Agricultural Reclamation, represented by farms, has played a demonstration and leading role in modern large-scale agriculture in recent years, and has initially established a modern agricultural industrial system dominated by large-scale planting, standardized production and industrial management.
On the outskirts of Youyi County, there is an Agricultural Machinery Expo Park covering an area of 350,000 square meters.
More than 140 sets (pieces) of agricultural machinery introduced and used by Heilongjiang Agricultural Reclamation over the years are displayed here.
These agricultural machinery and farms have witnessed the development of China's agricultural modernization.
She Xiaojia for Everyone - Anhui Hefei Jiangkou River Lianwei Mass Transfer Direct Attack-Xinhuanet
Xinhua News Agency, Hefei, July 26. Title: Give up a small family for everyone-Anhui Hefei Jiangkouhe Lianwei mass transfer direct attack
Xinhua News Agency reporters Chen Shangying, Wang Liwu and Liu Xiacun
At 4 o'clock in the afternoon on July 25, Fu Kunbao wore mud-covered rubber shoes. From the front room to the back room, he and his wife Zhou Yan were busy packing things back and forth.
" After receiving a call from the village cadre to transfer, I was still weeding in the field. "
Fu Kunbao said that he has transferred more than 60 acres of land and planted rice, and is now growing well. " I took the medicine yesterday, and I haven't cleaned up all the tools. "
Fu Kunbao pointed to the pesticide sprayer placed in the corner. " No one wants their home to be flooded. Give up a small home for everyone. "
In response to the continued high water level pressure and possible heavy rainfall in Chaohu Lake, Hefei City, Anhui Province is preparing to open flood diversion and storage in Jiangkouhe Lianwei, where Fu Kunbao's family is located, on the 26th.
Jiangkouhe Lianwei is located in Feixi County, next to Chaohu Dike.
There are thousands of villagers involved in Yandian Township and Sanhe Town who need to be transferred.
As of 16: 00 on the 25th, the water level of Chaohu Lake, China's fifth largest freshwater lake, remained at a high level of 13.2 meters, 0.7 meters above the guaranteed water level.
Fu Kunbao's kitchen is clean, with a pot of pumpkin head vegetables on the table, eggs and some stewed vegetables in the refrigerator.
" I didn't expect to move. The water in Jiangkou River looks good at present. "
Zhou Yan said that the family is a bungalow, and some large objects have not yet been decided where to put them.
" Pack up your valuables first. Large items such as refrigerators and TV sets can be temporarily placed in neighbors or relatives on high ground. "
Wang Liwen, a village cadre, gave Fu Kunbao advice.
Wang Liwen was responsible for the transfer and resettlement of 13 villagers, and notified each household to confirm each person's resettlement plan.
The nearest settlement to Fu Kunbao's home is Su Xiaoxiao School in Yandian Township, about 2 kilometers away.
In addition to the big items, the more than 1,000 catties of grain and some newly bought furniture were also a headache for Fu Kunbao and his wife.
" The food is going to be dragged to relatives' homes, and the furniture can't be moved. "
After a discussion, the couple put a stool under the newly bought bed and raised the bed by about half a meter.
At 6 o'clock in the afternoon, Fu Kunbao began to transport things to relatives' homes by tricycle, and Zhou Yan continued to clean up at home.
At 11 o'clock in the evening, the couple looked back and forth at home, turned on the switch, and prepared to go to the resettlement site.
" I hope the water will return soon. "
Fu Kunbao said.
At 9: 30 a.m. on July 26, the reporter saw at the scene of Jiangkouhe Lianwei that the local area had made various preparations before flood diversion.
