Xinhua News Agency, Moscow, July 25. According to the plan of the Russian Ministry of Defense, the upgraded version of the Russian armed helicopter (hereinafter referred to as Wuzhi) Ka-52, Ka-52M, will be transformed and shipped for the first time in December this year. The model will be greatly improved in reconnaissance, communications and weapon performance.
According to a recent report in Russia's Izvestia newspaper, Wuzhika-52M is called " Super Alligator. " Its development contract was signed by the Russian military and military units in April last year. At present, the first batch of two upgraded Wuzhika-52M is undergoing transformation and replacement at the Far East Helicopter Manufacturing Plant of Russia's " Progress " Aerospace Corporation. Its national testing and improvement work will be completed before October 2022.
According to Russian experts who understand the above-mentioned upgrade work, Wuzhika-52, the " predecessor " of " Super Alligator" , was officially installed in November 2011. Some weaknesses were exposed in the use of this model. This transformation and upgrade is just to " complement each other. "
The report said that compared with the Ka-52, the Ka-52M will partially adopt new protective materials that will not increase weight, and its pilot cockpit will be reinforced and equipped with new equipment to resist missile attacks, thus increasing the probability of battlefield survival; assemble more powerful generators to power more complex airborne electronic equipment; upgrade the photoelectric system to be able to detect and identify battlefield targets farther apart; The new light multi-purpose missile equipped with armored fighting vehicles and reinforced concrete fortifications has a range of 20 kilometers, which is about double the range of similar missiles used by Russia's active military forces; its defense weapons and communication equipment will be used to the maximum extent with Mi-28NM helicopter gunships that can attack air targets, thus making related maintenance simple and economical.
In addition, the Ka-52M will have more advanced electronic guidance systems, weapon targeting systems and navigation equipment.
Russian experts also said that it is worth noting that Ka-52M will be equipped with communication equipment to communicate with drones, so as to obtain real-time information transmitted by nearby drones in the air, such as displaying images taken by drones on the cockpit screen of the helicopter.
According to the plan, the pilots of the Ka-52M can directly control the drones they cooperate with, thus improving the pilots' grasp of the battlefield situation and the guidance of long-range missiles.
According to Russian media reports, Russian Deputy Defense Minister Krivoruchko said in December last year that the Russian Defense Ministry plans to purchase more than 110 Wuzhika-52Ms by 2027.
