Pursuing the Poetic " Yellow River Dream " -chinanews.com
(China's Poverty Reduction Story) Pursuing the Poetic " Yellow River Dream "
China News Service, Yinchuan, July 26 (Yang Di) " Jiuqu Yellow River thousands of miles of sand, waves and winds from the end of the world. "
The Yellow River, which aroused the pride of countless literati, gave birth to the beautiful and rich Ningxia Plain. Nowadays, Ningxia, which has the reputation of " blocking the south of the Yangtze River" , is adhering to the concept of " ecological priority and green development " and pursuing the poetic " Yellow River Dream. "
The beautiful " Bibo Dream " of the river
" The Yellow River in the world is rich in Ningxia. " The Yellow River flows through Ningxia for 397 kilometers and is the " mother river " for raising a party.
However, with the rapid advancement of industrialization and urbanization, the development, utilization, management and protection of rivers and lakes are out of balance, and chaos such as excessive sewage discharge, reclamation of lakes and encroachment on water areas are highlighted, resulting in black and smelly water bodies, excessive water quality, dirty environment and ecological degradation.
Now, Ningxia is promoting the diverse restoration of water ecology and striving to make the Yellow River beautiful and clear.
Water control should start from the source.
In Yinchuan, Ningxia, the local government adopted the method of " standard raising + pollution control + strict management" , all sewage in industrial parks was treated centrally, all urban sewage treatment plants were discharged according to Class A standard, and the black and odorous water bodies in urban built-up areas were basically eliminated, and the third batch of China's black and odorous water demonstration cities were successfully declared.
In addition, Ningxia fully implemented the river and lake chief system in 2017, and now it has achieved full coverage of the five-level river and lake chief responsibility system in districts, cities, counties and villages, and long patrolling of rivers and lakes has become the norm.
Gu Jincheng, 64, lives in a village by the Yellow River. He witnessed the changes in the Yellow River: " The water used to smell, but the smell disappeared after rectification. "
Gu Jincheng said that the ecological environment has improved and his life has become more comfortable. Now he often goes for a walk along the Yellow River with his family to feel the clear water and blue sky.
Sha Ouxiangji's " Wetland Dream "
Birds, green trees, plank roads, clear water... The beauty of Fan Zhongyan's " Sand Gulls Xiangji " has become a reality in the Yellow River Wetland Park in Yinchuan, Ningxia.
The Yellow River flows through Ningxia, forming river wetlands, lake wetlands, marsh wetlands and other wetlands along the way, which plays an important role in promoting the rational use of water resources and water ecological balance, and has also become an important international bird migration channel.
Since 2009, relevant departments in Ningxia have invested about 3.45 billion yuan in wetland protection projects. At present, Yinchuan wetland covers an area of 19,200 hectares, with a wetland protection rate of 78.5%. There are nearly 200 natural lakes and marsh wetlands, with 5 national wetland parks, 1 national urban wetland park, 6 autonomous region-level wetland parks and 8 municipal parks.
Lu Jinhu, deputy director of Yinchuan Wetland Protection Center, told reporters that wetland protection has increased biodiversity, especially in birds. " The gull is an endangered bird, with only more than 20,000 in the world, of which more than 2,000 live in Yinchuan Wetland. "
At the same time, Ningxia has delineated a 500-meter red line for the wetland protection areas on both sides of the Yinchuan section of the Yellow River in accordance with the law, stipulating that except for public welfare projects, no unit or individual may carry out development, construction and business activities within the scope of protection.
Zhao Shaoyong, deputy director of Yinchuan Water Conservancy Service Center, said that through pollution source control, comprehensive improvement of river and lake ecology and terminal wetland construction, the water quality of nine main drainage ditches in Ningxia has reached Class IV standards 100%. " Now the water is clear, the fish are swimming and the flowers are blooming. "
The " Drinking Water Dream " of Pu Huimin's Life
Yinchuan City, Ningxia, once had an " embarrassing " title: the only city along the Yellow River that " guarded the Yellow River and lacked water to drink. "
Since 2010, Yinchuan City has been facing the problem of persistent water shortage at the peak of summer. The " pain of water shortage " in the past ten years has become a painful summer experience for many high-rise residents. However, under the current situation that the major water sources are at the limit of overmining and a large area of groundwater overmining funnel area has been formed underground in the city, water shortage has become a difficult problem perplexing Yinchuan City.
Thanks to the improvement of the water quality of the Yellow River, drinking purified Yellow River water has become a good way to solve the drinking water problems of local residents.
Ding Ming, deputy director of Yinchuan Water Affairs Bureau, said that in order to improve the living and production water demand of urban and rural residents in Yinchuan, Ningxia started the water supply project on the western line of urban and rural areas in Yinchuan metropolitan area in due course, replacing the original underground water source with high-quality Yellow River water.
" On December 29, 2019, the water supply project officially provided water to the three districts of Yinchuan City. In 2020, residents of Minning Town and Helan County also drank the Yellow River. "
Ding Ming said that the Yinchuan water conservancy department will consider the transformation of the integration of regional rural drinking water and urban water supply. " In the next step, we will integrate all the scattered water supply points in rural areas into the western line water supply project. It is expected that the integrated urban and rural water supply in Yinchuan area will be basically realized by the end of this year. "
