" Compared with traditional solar power generation technology, its biggest advantage is that it can store the accumulated heat energy and generate electricity at night. "
Zhang Yong said that the 13-hour heat storage system configured in the project can keep the generator set in continuous and stable operation without being affected by light changes; it can also quickly participate in power grid peak regulation according to the peak and valley demand of power grid load.
After the project is fully completed, it can achieve an annual power generation of 198 million kWh, save more than 60,000 tons of standard coal each year, reduce more than 60 tons of sulfur dioxide, more than 60 tons of nitrogen oxides, about 20 tons of soot and more than 150,000 tons of carbon dioxide, and provide a steady stream of clean energy for the local area.
