Hao Yusheng, chief representative of Nasdaq Stock Exchange in China, said at the " 2020 Listed Company Leaders Summit China Stocks Branch " hosted by Snowball.
In April this year, the US Securities Regulatory Commission (SEC) and the US Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (PCAOB) issued the Statement on Audit Quality and the Important Role of Regulatory Access to Audit and Other International Information-Discussion on the Current Challenges of Information Access for US Listed Companies with Large Businesses in China.
The statement stated that although international cooperation and coordination have increased significantly in recent years, the problems of US regulators in obtaining information still exist, and the SEC and PCAOB still face legal and practical challenges; Corresponding to this document, the PCAOB website lists in detail the list of listed companies that have encountered audit obstacles and their audit institutions, and a large number of Chinese stock companies are listed.
In addition, in May this year, the US Senate passed the Foreign Company Accountability Act, which puts forward additional information disclosure requirements for foreign companies to list in the United States.
In Hao Yusheng's view, the crisis of Chinese stocks has not affected investors' appetite.
" When this news first came out, it caused everyone's panic. Everyone was asking if they could go public in the United States in the future, but later we found that these problems were not a problem for investors. Investors may ask these questions during the recent IPO roadshow in the United States, or even become standardized questions, but this has not been regarded by investors as an important factor in investing in a Chinese company.
It is recommended that everyone treat the current situation with a normal heart as much as possible.
Of course, this may seem to be the most serious situation in the past two years, but as far as investors' appetite is concerned, it has not been affected in any way.
So from now until the end of this year or before the US election, the upsurge of IPO in the United States will continue. "
On May 9 this year, Jinshan Cloud was officially listed on Nasdaq in the United States, becoming the first Chinese company to go to the United States for IPO after the epidemic.
" The listing of Jinshan Cloud gives great confidence to Chinese companies preparing for IPO. "
Hao Yusheng said.
According to the data report on Chinese stocks in the first half of 2020 released by Snowball, in the first half of this year, a total of 20 Chinese companies went to the United States for IPOs, an increase of 17.6% over the same period last year; In terms of total initial fund-raising, 20 companies raised a total of 2.725 billion yuan, up more than 52.4% compared with the same period last year; In terms of industry distribution, the number of IPOs in the health care industry in the first half of this year was outstanding, up 100% over the same period last year.
According to Hao Yusheng, the Chinese companies that went to the United States for IPO in the first half of this year are of high quality, and high-quality companies with excellent fundamentals and growth will be more favored by investors.
In the short, medium and long term, Hao Yusheng continues to be optimistic about the IPO of Ming Chinese companies in the United States.
" In the short term, the upsurge of IPO in the United States continues; in the medium term, Chinese companies have more choices, A shares, Hong Kong stocks, and US stocks. Everyone will consider the US election and Sino-US relations as market choices and time choices; In the long run, everything will return to normal, market fluctuations are cycles, both political and economic cycles, and will eventually return to the normal stage. The stock market has always been volatile. "
Hao Yusheng also said, " There are many uncertain factors this year, but for high-quality companies, no matter whether the market is good or bad, as long as they are solid and have growth that investors can see, other factors are relatively secondary. Investors need to invest in excellent Chinese companies. "
