With the decline in Yu'e Bao's earnings, the " post-90s " not only did not escape Yu'e Bao, but began to save money in a " retaliatory " manner?
The " Yu'ebao Post-90s Savings Report " (2020 version) recently released by the China New Economic Research Institute and Alipay shows that in the first half of the year, the " post-90s " are more likely to save money: the amount of money saved per capita increased by nearly 40% compared with 2019.
Interestingly, " post-90s " tend to save from a small sum of money, with 60% saving less than 20 yuan on average...
Saving money with Yu'e Bao has also become the saving habit of " post-90s. "
Data shows that among the 700 million Yu'e Bao users, 134 million are " post-90s. "
There are 174 million " post-90s " in China, that is to say, about 3 out of 4 " post-90s " in the country are saving money with Yu'e Bao.
At present, the 7-day annualized rate of return of monetary funds such as Yu'ebao has fallen to about 1.5% from a level higher than 2% at the beginning of the year.
Even so, it did not affect the pace of " post-90s " saving money.
Under the background of the improvement of Yu'e Bao's " money saving effect" , many young people who are used to using Yu'e Bao have directly transformed into " basic people. "
According to Alipay data, as of July 13, the number of new " basic people " on Alipay has more than doubled year-on-year in the past month, and more and more young people have achieved " advanced " financial management on Alipay.
Some analysts believe that the inflow of funds from Yu'ebao into the stock market is also an important reason for the clear decline in the share of monetary funds in June.
The report also shows that " post-90s " girls are more likely to save more money, with an average of 20% higher than that of boys. Among the users who hold funds on Alipay platform, 60% are men, and women tend to choose more robust financial management methods than men.
After saving money, what are the plans of the " post-90s "?
Alipay data shows that the " post-90s " have the habit of saving money for their goals, and the largest number of users take travel as their saving goal.
Affected by the epidemic, many " post-90s " save money to prepare for travel after the epidemic; the reopening of cinemas also provides a new way to switch from saving money to consumption.
