The trade ministers of APEC members agreed that it is necessary to discuss how to reduce non-tariff barriers that restrict trade in necessary commodities, and reiterated their commitment to promote the necessary cross-border movement of people without affecting the measures taken to prevent the spread of the epidemic.
The meeting also issued a declaration on promoting the circulation of necessary commodities.
The declaration stated that the economies will ensure that the trade measures they take in response to the epidemic comply with WTO regulations, and promise to take actions in reducing non-tariff trade barriers and trade promotion to promote the necessary commodity flow under the epidemic.
