The report says the shared accommodation market has picked up since March-chinanews.com
(Reporter Yang Zhaokui) The " China Shared Accommodation Development Report 2020 " (hereinafter referred to as the " Report ") recently released by the Sharing Economy Research Center of the National Information Center shows that due to the impact of the epidemic, the transaction volume of China's shared accommodation market decreased by 72.1% year-on-year in the first five months of 2020.
However, the shared accommodation market began to pick up in March, and the market transaction volume, order volume and reception number gradually recovered.
The " Report " shows that the transaction volume of the shared accommodation market has declined significantly. On the one hand, due to the sharp decline in the demand for travel accommodation under the prevention and control of the epidemic, the order volume has decreased sharply. The total order volume in the first five months has decreased by 65% year-on-year, and the number of receptions has decreased by 63% year-on-year. On the other hand, the weak demand has also led to a relatively obvious decline in overnight prices, with the average overnight price in the first five months falling by 16% year-on-year.
However, the market transaction volume in March, April and May increased by 78%, 199% and 35% respectively; the number of orders increased by 141%, 152% and 50% respectively; and the number of receptions increased by 81%, 112% and 28% respectively.
The " Report " pointed out that the development of the shared accommodation industry is promising for a long time, but there are still many uncertainties in the near future.
In this regard, Yu Fengxia, deputy director of the Sharing Economy Research Center of the National Information Center, told the Workers' Daily reporter that the development of shared accommodation needs stronger policy support. On the one hand, it is necessary to implement the policies already issued in the early stage, further strengthen policy publicity and focus on creating a better business environment; on the other hand, it is necessary to further strengthen policy guidance and support from stimulating consumer demand, enriching the supply of tourism accommodation services, innovating service methods and strengthening cooperation between the government and platform enterprises.
