chinanews.com, Xiamen, July 26 (Yang Fushan, Zhang Shushan, Xu Jingyi) The Department of Vascular Surgery, Shanghai Changhai Hospital, Naval Military Medical University, China's famous vascular surgery center, signed a contract with the Department of Vascular Surgery, Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University on the 25th to jointly set up a collaboration center to promote exchanges and cooperation between the two sides in the field of vascular surgery, especially in the field of acute and severe aortic disease.
Zhongshan Hospital affiliated to Xiamen University said that after the vascular surgery of the two hospitals formally form a cooperative unit, they will carry out remote consultation, formulate treatment plans with Changhai Hospital in real-time online consultation, select and send talents for further training, and jointly carry out surgical technical exchanges and teaching visits every week; For complex cases, Changhai experts can be invited to the hospital to perform operations according to the needs of patients, so that patients in southwestern Fujian can enjoy the top medical resources in China without leaving the province.
The two hospitals will also work together to carry out surgical innovation and scientific research, aortic disease popularization and early screening, etc.
A special seminar on aorta sponsored by Beijing Health Promotion Association and hosted by Zhongshan Hospital affiliated to Xiamen University was held in Xiamen on the same day.
At the same time, the two well-known hospitals in Shanghai and Xiamen held a signing ceremony for the Vascular Surgery Collaboration Center and announced the formation of a cooperative unit to jointly improve the treatment level of vascular surgery-related diseases in southwest Fujian.
The Department of Vascular Surgery of Shanghai Changhai Hospital is the only institute of vascular surgery in the army and the only clinical medical center of vascular system diseases in Shanghai. It is also the first national key discipline of vascular surgery. It has led the establishment of the Endovascular Professional Committee of the Chinese Medical Association and is a top team with deep accumulation in the industry.
Professor Huang Xiaojin, Director of Vascular Surgery, Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University, was interviewed by the media.
The Department of Vascular Surgery, Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University, is the first independent discipline of vascular surgery in Fujian Province. It has long been committed to the diagnosis and treatment of aortic and peripheral vascular diseases. In 2018, it was approved to build a provincial key clinical specialty.
In the treatment of aortic diseases, in addition to the treatment of dissecting aneurysms and aortic aneurysms, he has extensive experience in emergency ruptured aortic aneurysms.
" The Department of Vascular Surgery of Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University is very outstanding in this region in terms of the history of development, the breadth, difficulty and complexity of the operation, so this time we set up a collaboration center. In addition to the aorta, we can also carry out all-round in-depth cooperation in medicine, teaching and scientific research in the diagnosis and treatment of lower limb arteries, carotid arteries and other diseases. "
Professor Feng Rui, deputy director of vascular surgery at Shanghai Changhai Hospital, said.
Zhongshan Hospital Affiliated to Xiamen University and Shanghai Changhai Hospital signed a contract to establish the " Li Zhaoshen Famous Doctor Studio " in the Department of Gastroenterology in 2018.
Professor Huang Xiaojin, director of vascular surgery of the hospital, said in an interview with chinanews.com that the vascular surgery of the hospital has also had a long history of exchanges with Changhai Hospital. This time, the two hospitals formally formed a cooperative unit, bringing cooperation and exchanges between the two sides to a new level.
He said that the hospital will regularly invite Shanghai experts to Xiamen to carry out surgical technical exchanges, teaching visits, difficult case discussions, etc., and further carry out remote consultations. Currently, it plans to conduct remote consultations once a week; In addition, the department will also select and send personnel for further training and exchanges to strengthen the training and development of subject talents.
The reporter learned at the meeting that vascular disease is the leading cause of death in China. As the main artery of various organs of the human body, the aorta flows from the heart to the whole body and plays an important role.
The occurrence of aortic disease is often accompanied by high risk, high mortality and high difficulty of treatment. The thickest section of the aorta is up to 4cm in diameter. Once hemangioma is formed, rupture occurs, or vascular intima rupture produces dissection, it will cause massive hemorrhage, which is very dangerous.
In recent years, with the change of people's lifestyle and the acceleration of the pace of life, China has become the world's largest country with hypertension, and aortic diseases have also increased. Nowadays, with the development of surgical technology and industrial materials, the treatment of aortic diseases continues to develop in a minimally invasive, rapid and efficient direction.
Doctors can puncture from the thigh and place stents in the aorta to properly " divert " the blood flow, so as to avoid the impact on aneurysms or ruptured dissections, and achieve good therapeutic results. Some operations even require local anesthesia.
This academic seminar invited more than ten domestic experts to discuss the new progress in the treatment of aortic diseases, and carried out cutting-edge technical training and difficult case discussions in the form of a conference salon.
The reporter learned at the meeting that with the development of surgical technology and industrial materials, the current treatment of aortic diseases continues to develop in a minimally invasive, rapid and efficient direction.
