The longest high-speed railway tunnel in the Three Gorges Reservoir Area runs through-chinanews.com
2020-07-26 17: 34: 48 Source: China News Network Author: Chen Haifeng Editor: Chen Haifeng
The picture shows the construction site of the Small Three Gorges Tunnel.
Photo courtesy of China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Company
China News Service, Chongqing, July 26 (Reporter Han Lu) The reporter learned from the China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Co., Ltd. on the 26th that the Zhengwan High-speed Railway Small Three Gorges Tunnel, with a total length of about 18.9 kilometers, was completed on the same day.
It is understood that the Small Three Gorges Tunnel is not only the longest high-speed railway tunnel in the Three Gorges Reservoir Area, but also the longest single-hole double-track high-speed railway tunnel with a design speed of 350 km / h among the projects currently under construction in China.
Zhengzhou-Wanzhou high-speed railway is located in the three provinces and cities of Henan, Hubei and Chongqing, connecting Beijing-Guangzhou and Xulan high-speed railway in the north of Zhengzhou, and connecting Yu-Wanzhou high-speed railway to Chongqing in the south of Wanzhou. It is an important part of China's " eight vertical and eight horizontal " high-speed railway network.
The Zhengwan High-speed Railway Small Three Gorges Tunnel was completed on the 26th.
The picture shows through the scene.
The Zhengzhou-Wanzhou high-speed railway starts in Zhengzhou City, Henan Province, and runs southwest through Pingdingshan City, Nanyang City, and Xiangyang City in Hubei Province to Wanzhou District of Chongqing City. The new line is about 818 kilometers long, with a design speed of 350 kilometers per hour, and about 184 kilometers in Chongqing.
Among them, the Zhengzhou-Xiangyang section has been opened for operation in advance on December 1, 2019, and the Chongqing section is stepping up its construction.
The Small Three Gorges Tunnel, which runs through the whole line on the 26th, is a full-line control project of Zhengwan High-speed Railway. The project is located at the junction of Fengjie County and Wushan County in Chongqing City, with a total length of about 18.9 kilometers and a maximum buried depth of 890 meters.
Construction of the tunnel began in February 2017 and was completed on July 26, 2020.
According to Wang Guojun, head of Zhengwan high-speed railway tunnel design at China Railway Second Academy Engineering Group Co., Ltd., the survey and design party, the small Three Gorges Tunnel is located in very complex topographic and geological conditions, facing risks such as karst, mud gushing and large deformation of soft rock. It is a Class I high-risk tunnel, and its design and construction are extremely difficult.
" During the construction of the project, we used geological survey method, geophysical exploration method and advanced drilling method to advance geological prediction, and adopted special design plans for more than 30 karst caves of various types. For example, a bridge with a length of 24 meters was designed and built to span a large karst cave with a longitudinal length of more than 10 meters and a depth of more than 55 meters in the tunnel to avoid tunnel settlement. " Wang Guojun said.
According to the introduction of the China Railway Tunnel Bureau, during the construction of the tunnel, the combination of drainage and blocking was adopted. Through the construction of horizontal tunnels, grouting to block water, strengthening the structural support of the tunnel and building a sewage treatment station, the orderly progress of the project was ensured, and the damage of construction drainage to the water body of the Small Three Gorges Scenic Area was avoided. At the same time, the construction problems such as bad geology such as large deformation of soft rock with a length of 7 kilometers and multiple mud gushing with a maximum daily water inflow of 157,000 cubic meters were successfully overcome.
After the Zhengzhou-Wanzhou high-speed railway is completed and opened to traffic, it will become a new convenient and fast passenger passage from southwest China to the Central Plains, North China and Northeast China. It is of great significance to improve the capacity and quality of the northeast railway passage in southwest China, improve the layout of the regional road network, speed up the development of tourism resources and urbanization along the route, promote regional coordinated development, and promote the implementation of the western development strategy.
