In the first half of this year, in the face of the impact of the COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic, my country made overall plans to promote epidemic prevention and control and economic and social development. The situation of epidemic prevention and control continued to improve, the steady economic recovery was obvious, the employment and price performance closely related to people's livelihood were generally stable, and the Chinese economy handed over a report card of economic operation with temperature.
In the first two months of this year, the surveyed unemployment rate rose.
Especially in February, the production and operation activities of many enterprises were basically in a state of shutdown, the employment demand of enterprises decreased, recruitment was delayed or cancelled, and the surveyed unemployment rate in cities and towns increased.
With the gradual improvement of the epidemic prevention and control situation, the production and living order of the whole society has been continuously restored.
The Party Central Committee adheres to the general tone of seeking progress while maintaining stability, further strengthens macro-policy hedging, comprehensively strengthens the employment priority policy, and actively promotes the work of assisting and stabilizing posts and expanding employment.
China has increased its policy of hedging and stabilizing jobs, played a combination of " reduction, reduction, slow return and compensation " policies, phased reduction and reduction of three social insurance unit contributions, allowed deferred payment of social insurance premiums, expanded the benefits of the policy of post return of unemployment insurance for small and medium-sized enterprises, and provided absorption subsidies and internship subsidies for enterprises to absorb the employment of key groups.
