Data show that the total urban employment in June increased by more than 19% compared with February, and most industries reached the pre-epidemic level; the average weekly working hours of enterprise employees reached 46.8 hours, 6.6 hours higher than in February and 0.1 hours higher than in January.
Prices are also related to thousands of households.
