Weining County, where Yina Town is located, has a certain popularity in the surrounding areas because of its low latitude, high altitude, sufficient light and large temperature difference between day and night. However, because of its small size and many spots, it has not been able to sell at a good price and form an industrial scale.
Yina Town used to be a poor township that " packed the valley with potato to spend the spring and autumn. " Ten years ago, the local poverty incidence rate was as high as 25.8%.
In the critical period of poverty alleviation entering a decisive battle, it is urgent to change traditional planting habits, adjust the industrial structure and increase farmers' income.
After many visits, Chen Chao, secretary of the Party Committee of Yina Town, and a group of people in the town believed that industrial development could no longer follow the old path.
To this end, Yina Town introduced leading enterprises to grow apples in a modern way.
Hou Jianwen, deputy general manager of Weining Chaoyue Agriculture Co., Ltd., came to Yina Town from Shaanxi in 2015 for research. He saw the local planting conditions at a glance and began to plant apple trees in the local area in 2016.
At first, the village mobilized Li Yuanzhong to transfer the land to plant apple trees, and the Li Yuanzhong and his wife murmured in their hearts: " After so many years of apples, they have never seen anyone in the village who has grown apples and made a fortune. "
" The apples planted are dwarf apples, which will not make the apple trees grow too tall. "
To Li Yuanzhong's surprise, a new method was adopted for apple planting this time. Irrigation pipes were laid under each apple tree, and water and fertilizer were poured to the roots. When the fruit was harvested in autumn, the tractor drove directly into the orchard and could pick the fruit standing.
At present, the Apple base has gradually entered a high-yield period, and the market is as expected by Hou Jianwen. Apples are not worried about selling and are deeply loved by consumers in Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou and other cities.
The growing apple industry has brought new changes to Li Yuanzhong's life. Although he is still farming, he has a new source of income.
Li Yuanzhong's family has more than 9 acres of land transferred to the apple base. Every year, in addition to the guaranteed land transfer fee, there is a profit dividend after hanging the fruit. The couple usually work in the base. " One person can get 80 yuan a day and have work all the year round. "
Li Yuanzhong told reporters that last year's profit dividend received more than 2,800 yuan, plus land transfer fees and the couple's labor income, and the family's income was more than 80,000 yuan. " You don't have to worry about food and clothing, and a well-off life has already passed. "
" At present, initial results have been achieved. The annual output value of 1 mu of apples exceeds 15,000 yuan, which is about 10 times that of corn. "
Chen Chao told reporters that 20,000 mu of apples have been planted in the whole town of Yina, 6,000 mu in Zhonghai Village alone, covering 4,056 households and 17,200 people, including 656 households and 2,952 poor households. The annual salary is more than 6 million yuan, which really realizes that the base is built at home and there is no need to go out to work.
Li Yuanzhong, whose pockets are bulging day by day, also began to realize his " wish. "
During the Lunar New Year this year, Li Yuanzhong bought an off-road vehicle and now drives to and from work every day. " There are still more than ten acres of land at home. When the next step is to expand the scale of the Apple base, all of it will be transferred to them, and the income will be even more. "
