Membrane separation technology helps crack the " greenhouse effect " -chinanews.com
Membrane separation technology helps crack the " greenhouse effect "
Schematic diagram of new mixed matrix membrane preparation technology
News from our newspaper reporter Shang Rui reported: A few days ago, the Tianjin University Atmospheric Environment and Bioenergy Team has made significant progress on the " membrane separation method to capture carbon dioxide " and successfully developed a new mixed matrix membrane preparation technology, which greatly improves the carbon dioxide capture performance of membrane materials.
Relevant results have been published as the cover article of the international journal Greenhouse Gas: Science and Technology.
The " greenhouse effect " is a major environmental problem perplexing human development, and carbon dioxide emissions are the culprit responsible for the " greenhouse effect. "
How to efficiently capture and utilize the carbon dioxide emitted by humans is the focus of attention of scientists.
" Membrane separation method " is an emerging carbon dioxide capture technology. It separates carbon dioxide gas with the help of membrane materials, which has the characteristics of high efficiency, energy saving and simple operation.
How to make the membrane material " breathe deeply " and improve the efficiency of gas separation is the bottleneck and difficulty in capturing carbon dioxide by membrane separation method.
The scientific research team of Tianjin University innovated ideas and explored the influence of different solvents on membrane gas separation performance through repeated experiments.
The experimental results show that with N-methylpyrrolidone as the preparation solvent, the distribution of carbon nanotubes in the membrane material is more uniform and " more breathable" , which effectively improves the gas separation efficiency and rate of the membrane material.
The carbon dioxide separation performance of the mixed matrix membrane prepared by this new technology is close to the theoretical separation upper limit of this kind of membrane material.
" The new technology provides a new idea for capturing carbon dioxide by membrane separation. "
Li Run, a member of the atmospheric environment and bioenergy team of Tianjin University, said: " We hope that this technology can provide strong support for future coal-fired power plants and chemical enterprises to deal with flue gas and play an important role in controlling greenhouse gas emissions. "
Understand what is the professional grade difference before volunteering to fill in the report-chinanews.com
2020-07-27 02: 22: 36 Source: Chongqing Morning Post Author: Yu Xiao Editor: Yu Xiao
Understand what is a professional grade difference before volunteering to fill in the report
Every year, there are students or parents who do not understand the terms involved in the voluntary application, which affects the voluntary application.
This year, Beijing Jiaotong University, Beijing University of Science and Technology, Beijing University of Posts and Telecommunications, Beijing Forestry University, and Beijing University of Chemical Technology jointly issued the 2020 enrollment policy to cancel the professional grade difference.
What is the meaning of professional grade difference and what is its significance in voluntary reporting?
There are three ways of professional allocation rules
Experts remind that before filling in the application, you must carefully read the " Admissions Regulations " of your favorite school to understand the admission rules of colleges and universities, including the proportion of file transfer, professional allocation rules, etc.
Professional allocation rules refer to three ways of professional admission: professional priority, score priority, and professional grade difference after colleges and universities are transferred.
The specific method used by colleges and universities will be specified in the " Admissions Regulations. "
However, the admission principle of some colleges and universities is that the total score is first, and there is no grade difference between majors.
That is to say, candidates in the admission range will be queued up according to the total score. When the score does not reach the first professional voluntary admission score line, it will be seen whether it has reached the second professional voluntary admission score line, and so on until the last professional volunteer is admitted. There is no level difference between the professional volunteers.
The so-called " professional level difference " means that when colleges and universities arrange candidates' majors, they determine the admission majors of volunteer candidates of different majors according to one or several score values announced in the enrollment regulations. This score value is the " professional level difference. "
That is, the score difference between the first professional volunteer and the non-first professional volunteer in the college, and the grade difference score between the professional volunteers, such as 3 points, 2 points, 1 point, etc.
For example.
Suppose student Xiaoming applied for college A and scored 560 points. His professional volunteers are: computer, international trade, automation, mechanical engineering, and e-commerce. The professional admission of college A adopts the method of professional grade difference, which is divided into 2 points, 1 point, 1 point, and 0 point.
In the professional allocation, if Xiaoming's first professional volunteer meets the professional admission requirements and the major has a planned balance, then Xiaoming is admitted to the " computer " major; if the computer is not admitted, his score will be subtracted by 2 points, and the score of 558 points will be sorted with the candidates who volunteer to apply for " international trade " in the first major to determine whether they meet the professional admission conditions; if it is still not satisfied, the score will be subtracted by 1 point (that is, 557 points) for the " automatic " admission of the third professional volunteer; if it is still not satisfied, the score will be subtracted by 1 point (that is, 556 points) for admission to the fourth major. If the follow-up major still cannot meet its professional wishes, the points will not be reduced, and so on.
Different universities have different professional grade differences
With the popularization of parallel volunteering, many colleges and universities have cancelled the professional level difference, but some colleges and universities still retain this method this year. According to the " Admissions Regulations " published by each school, more than 20 universities have set up professional level differences this year.
For example, Sichuan Agricultural University, Shandong University of Science and Technology, Heilongjiang University of Traditional Chinese Medicine, Jiangsu University of Science and Technology, Jiangxi Normal University, Chengdu Medical University, Northeast Dianli University, Jimei University, Nanjing Medical University, Nanjing University of Technology, Ningxia University, Shandong University of Technology, China Civil Aviation Flight College, etc.
In these colleges and universities, each university has different professional grades.
Some colleges and universities have a grade difference in each major, such as Ningxia University. Candidates whose files have been submitted to the school will be admitted according to the order in which the candidates fill in their professional volunteers.
And some universities have set up different professional level differences between different majors.
For example, Jimei University, the total score of professional volunteer difference is 4 points, that is, the difference between the first professional volunteer and other professional volunteers is 3 points, there is no difference between other professional volunteers, which is regarded as parallel volunteer, and the difference between other professional volunteers and transfer professional volunteers is 1 point.
When filling in their volunteers, candidates and parents must carefully read the admission policy of the reported school to see if there is a professional grade difference and what is the form of the grade difference. While fully considering the scores, they should also reasonably analyze the school and major to be selected. If the college clearly adopts the grade difference method for admission in the admissions charter, candidates should pay attention to the gradient between the majors when choosing a major to improve the admission probability.
